			<h2>PRIVACY NOTICE DISCLOSURE</h2>
			<p>Pursuant to what is set forth in the Ley Federal de Protección de Datos Personales en Posesión de los Particulares (hereinafter referred to as &ldquo;the Law &quot;), we would like to inform you the following:</p>
			<h3>1.- INDIVIDUAL OR ENTITY IN CHARGE OF THE PERSONAL DATA</h3>
			<p>Pernod Ricard México, S.A. de C.V., (hereinafter referred to as &quot;PRM&quot;), having as its address for the purposes of the present Privacy Notice Disclosure that located at Paseo de los Tamarindos 100, piso 3, Colonia Bosques de las Lomas, Delegación Cuajimalpa, México Distrito Federal, Código Postal 05120, will be the entity in charge of the personal data to be provided to the same by the relevant individuals (personas físicas, in Spanish) (hereinafter referred to as the &ldquo;Holder&rdquo; or &ldquo;Holder´s&rdquo;). </p>
			<h3>2.- PERSONAL DATA REQUIRED FROM THE HOLDER</h3>
			<p>For the purposes referred to in the present Privacy Notice Disclosure, <strong>PRM</strong> may collect the personal data from the Holder, such as its name (official ID, as well as the image from the Holder when entering into <strong>PRM</strong> facilities through security and video-surveillance cameras), address, landline phone, Federal Taxpayers&rsquo; Registry (RFC, in Spanish), bank account number and occupation or  professional activity (hereinafter and jointly referred to as &ldquo;Personal Data&rdquo;) in any of the following manners: i) when the Holder personally or directly provides them; ii) when <strong>PRM</strong> indirectly obtains them; iii) when the Holder uses <strong>PRM</strong>&rsquo;s website or online services; and/or iv) when such data are obtained by <strong>PRM</strong> through sources allowed by the legislation.</p>
			<p>The Personal Data Holder shall ensure that the data personally or directly provided to <strong>PRM</strong> by the former are full and accurate. The former shall also provide <strong>PRM</strong> with notice of any modifications of the same in order to comply with the obligation of keeping the information updated.</p>
			<h3>3.- REASONS TO COLLECT PERSONAL DATA</h3>
			<p>Information on Personal Data, which is collected by <strong>PRM</strong> from the Holder, shall be used as follows: <strong>i)</strong> to comply with the contracts entered into between <strong>PRM</strong> and the Holder (hereinafter referred to as &ldquo;the Contracts&rdquo;); <strong>ii)</strong> to identify the Holder; <strong>iii)</strong> to manage the Contracts; i<strong>v)</strong> to update the Holder&rsquo;s data; <strong>v)</strong> to provide security to <strong>PRM</strong>&lsquo;s facilities and to the Holders entering into the same. Such requirements are needed in order to comply with the obligations resulting from the legal relationship between <strong>PRM</strong> and the Holder.</p>
			<p>Regarding the Personal Data of those Holders which in the past had a relationship with <strong>PRM&rsquo;</strong>s but not anymore we inform to that Holders that <strong>PRM </strong>only retains their Personal Data in accordance with the provisions of Article 25 of the Law, during the lockout period<span class="sprRmn">1</span> established in the Law, so that, after such period your Personal Data will be deleted.</p>
			<h3>4.- TIMEFRAMES, REFERRALS, AND TRANSFERS</h3>
			<p>Timeframes to manage the Holder&rsquo;s Personal Data shall depend on the legal relationship between the former and <strong>PRM</strong>, as well as on the obligations required by the legislation in force, the relevant authorities, and <strong>PRM</strong>&rsquo;s internal policies. However, concerning the Personal Data related to the Holder&rsquo;s images that are captured using video-surveillance cameras, such information shall be kept by <strong>PRM</strong> only for a term of 30 (thirty) to 60 (sixty) business days following the date on which it has been obtained.</p>
			<p>The information delivered to <strong>PRM</strong> shall be kept and protected by the latter pursuant to what is set forth in the legislation in force and <strong>PRM</strong>&rsquo;s internal policies in order to keep such information as confidential in nature. </p>
			<p>Pursuant to what is established by the Law, <strong>PRM</strong> shall provide access to the Holder&rsquo;s Personal Data (by means of referrals) to those individuals acting as Data Controllers<span class="sprRmn">2</span>, such as <strong>PRM</strong>&rsquo;s business partners or service suppliers that have a legal relationship with the former and that, as a result of such a legal relationship, need to know the information and commit to keep the same strictly confidential and reserved, and who shall state they know the terms and conditions of the present Privacy Notice Disclosure and commit to comply with the same.</p>
			<p>On the other hand, <strong>PRM</strong> provides to its affiliates and subsidiaries the Personal Data from the Holders, in order to comply with the legal relationships that <strong>PRM</strong> has with such companies. Such transfers shall not require the consent from the Holder under article 37 of the Law. </p>
			<p>If the Personal Data under protection should be required by any authorities or if they should be delivered to the latter pursuant to the legislation in force, such data shall be available for the same pursuant to the Law and such a transfer shall not require the consent from the Holder under article 37 of such a legal framework.</p>
			<h3>5.- RIGHTS OF PERSONAL DATA ACCESS, CORRECTION, CANCELLATION, OPPOSITON, RENEWAL, AND LIMITATION.</h3>
			<p>Holders of information shall have the right to require the access, correction, revocation, cancellation, or opposition, as well as limitation of use or disclosure of their data, by means of:</p>
			<p>a.- A written application submitted to the Vice-presidency of Legal and Corporate Issues from Pernod Ricard México, S.A. de C.V., to the following address: Paseo de los Tamarindos 100, piso 3, Colonia Bosques de las Lomas, Delegación Cuajimalpa, México Distrito Federal, Código Postal 05120, from 10:00 to 17:00 hours, in business days; or</p>
			<p>b.- An application sent to the electronic mail <a href="mailto:mxdatospersonales@pernod-ricard.com" class="lnk">mxdatospersonales@pernod-ricard.com</a></p>
			<p><strong>PRM</strong> shall provide an answer to the applications from the information Holder, provided exceptions included in the Law do not apply and the applicant complies with what is set forth in article 29 of the legal framework establishing the requirements for the applications submitted by the Holders.</p>
			<p>In order for <strong>PRM</strong> to process the application form a Holder regarding access, correction, revocation, cancellation, opposition, and/or limitation of use or disclosure of its data, the latter shall attach the following information and documentation to its application:</p>
			<ul class="lwr-Ltn">
				<li>The name of the Holder, as well as its address and any other means in order for <strong>PRM</strong> to provide the answer to its application.</li>
				<li>The documents evidencing its identity or status of the Holder legal representatives (official ID of the Holder or legal representative and the power of attorney of the latter). </li>
				<li>An accurate and precise description of the Personal Data for which the right of access, correction, revocation, cancellation, opposition, limitation of use or disclosure is requested, as well as any other data or document that may help to locate the relevant Personal Data. </li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>PRM </strong>shall provide an answer to the application of a Holder regarding the access, correction, revocation, cancellation, opposition, and/or limitation of use or disclosure of its data within the terms established by the Law, that is, within the twenty (20) days following the reception of the Holder&rsquo;s application. Such a term may be extended by <strong>PRM</strong> pursuant to what is set forth in article 32 of the Law. </p>
			<p>Obligation of information access shall be deemed as complied with by <strong>PRM</strong> if, in case of being requested by the Holder, its Personal Data are made available to the latter at <strong>PRM</strong>&rsquo;s address during the term of 15 (fifteen) business days following the date on which the Holder is provided with the answer to its application, or by means of any of the manners set forth in article 33 of the Law, which will be notified to the Holder in such an answer to its application.</p>
			<h3>6.- MODIFICATIONS TO THE PRIVACY NOTICE DISCLOSURE</h3>
			<p>In case <strong>PRM</strong> requires to use its Personal Data for purposes other than the ones agreed upon according to the legal relationship with the Holder and in the present Privacy Notice Disclosure, or if the same requires from the Holder Personal Data other than those stated in the present Privacy Notice Disclosure, the Holder shall be notified in writing, by phone, electronically, or by means of any other visual, audio, or optical means, or any other allowed by the technology currently or in the future, explaining the new uses that are pretended for such an information, in order to obtain its consent under the Law. With the present Privacy Notice Disclosure, the information Holders are duly informed about the data being collected from them and for what purposes, as well as about the fact that such a Privacy Notice Disclosure may be looked up at all times at <strong>PRM</strong>&rsquo;s website <a href="http://www.pernod-ricard-mexico.com" class="lnk">www.pernod-ricard-mexico.com</a></p>
			<p><strong>INVIDO</strong> reserves its right to modify this Privacy Notice Disclosure in order to adapt the same to the latest jurisprudences or legislative innovations, as well as to trade practices. In such cases, the relevant changes shall be posted in the website <a href="http://www.pernod-ricard-mexico.com" class="lnk">www.pernod-ricard-mexico.com</a></p>
			<p>This Privacy Notice Disclosure, as well as the general compliance with the Law by <strong>PRM</strong>, shall be ruled by the legislation in force and applicable in the Mexican United States. Any controversies resulting from such an application shall be settled by the Federal Institute for Information Access and Data Protection (IFAI, in Spanish) or before the relevant Courts from Mexico City, Federal District.</p>
			<p>Latest update: March 7th, 2013.</p>
			<p>I hereby agree and authorize that my Personal Data are handled pursuant to the terms and conditions of the present Privacy Notice Disclosure.</p>
			<p>_______________________________(Name and signature)</p>
