			<small><span class="sprRmn">1</span>Article 3 of  the Ley Federal de Protección de Datos Personales en Posesión de los  Particulares establishes that the &ldquo;lockout period&rdquo; is: The period of time on  which the person who obtains the Personal Data of a Holder may keep such  Personal Data after the fulfillment of the purpose for which it was collected, with  the sole intention of identifying any kind of responsibilities related to the  Personal Data treatment. The lockout period corresponds to the legal  prescription term established in any applicable law for any kind of  responsibilities that may be a consequence of the Personal Data treatment. At  the end of this period the corresponding database shall be cancelled. </small><br>
			<small><span class="sprRmn">2</span>Article 3 of  the Ley Federal de Protección de Datos Personales en Posesión de los  Particulares establishes that the Data Controller is the individual or entity that  individually or jointly handles personal data on behalf of the Individual or  Entity in Charge of such data. </small>
		</div>
